org.glassfish.security.services.api.authorization

Interface AzResult

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AzResultImpl

    public interface AzResult
    The AzResult class represents the result of an authorization decision. The result includes three distinct results: A result status, which indicates whether the call was successful or not, and may indicate a reason for a failed call; an authorization decision, which is valid only if the status is "OK", and obligations, which represent actions the calling code must take if it proceeds to access the resource in question. Obligations are expressed as attributes; the meaning of any specific obligation is established by an out-of-band agreement between the PDP and the PEP.
